==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cistercian
<hw>Cis*ter"cian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>Cistercium</ets>. F. <ets>C⟦icir⟧teaux</ets>, a convent not far
from Dijon, in France: cf. F. <ets>cistercien</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A monk of the prolific branch of the Benedictine
Order, established in 1098 at C⟦icir⟧teaux, in France, by Robert, abbot
of Molesme. For two hundred years the Cistercians followed the rule of
St. Benedict in all its rigor.</def> -- <def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to the Cistercians.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

